sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor User
  participant UI as Web UI
  participant App as Flask Handler
  participant Intent as Intent Router
  participant Adp as DB Adapter
  participant LLM as LLM Router
  participant Val as Validator
  participant DB as Database

  User->>UI: Type natural-language command
  UI->>App: POST /command
  App->>Intent: normalize and match command
  alt Hardcoded introspection command
    Intent->>Adp: describe / show FKs / indexes ...
    Adp->>DB: PRAGMA / catalog query
    DB-->>Adp: metadata
    Adp-->>App: structured result (no LLM)
  else Natural-language query
    App->>Adp: get_schema() (cols, PKs, FKs, indexes, 3 sample rows)
    Adp-->>App: schema text
    App->>LLM: prompt(schema, history, command)
    LLM-->>App: generated SQL + explanation
    App->>Val: classify_query() and is_safe()
    alt READ / SYSTEM and safe
      App->>Val: RBAC is_allowed(role, task)
      App->>Adp: execute(paginated SQL)
      Adp->>DB: run query
      DB-->>Adp: rows
      Adp-->>App: columns + rows
      App-->>UI: results table
    else WRITE / SCHEMA
      App-->>UI: Review page (editable SQL)
      User->>UI: Confirm / Dry-Run
      UI->>App: POST /execute
      App->>Val: re-check is_safe + RBAC
      App->>App: take_snapshot() (auto backup)
      App->>Adp: execute(write)
      Adp->>DB: commit
      App-->>UI: success + undo option
    else Unsafe / blocked
      App-->>UI: blocked (logged)
    end
  end
